<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002412.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Jehu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I've started a Barb Warrior (level  5)---one of the two classes/races I always wanted to play but was cautioned against.  My other characters are a level 26 Human Druid and a level 18 High Elf Paladin.  One thing I've noticed about my dim-witted barbarian is he seldom gains skill in either 1HS or 2HS.  My defensive and offensive skills go up at a nice clip each level but I am lucky to get 2 skill increases per level with my weapons.  I am not a mega-twink but I am twinked with banded, a langseax and a BBC.  My Paladin was also twinked with banded, a BBC and a FS scimitar (now a silvery war axe).  The high intelligence of the High-elf Pally allowed me to max out both slashing melee skills within the first two bubbles of experience after making each level.  I have to spend training points to see any real skill increase with my Barbarian.  Is this something I need to get used to or is it just a statistical oddity I am going through?  I expected the skill increase to come slower with a 60 int, but I didn't expect it to be this bad.     <P>Thanks<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Tappen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Around 8th level you'll be taking long enough to level that your skills will start catching up.  At least until 35th level or so when skill raises become rare again.  Don't worry.  Dexterity seems to help in combat skill gains, though that's just personal unscientific experience.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Rani</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Get some +DEX items to wear. Abashi(or was it GZ) said specifically that dex affected skill gains for 1 hand slashing, before they decided to not explain stats any further.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Arek of the Nexus Knights</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><BR> For what it's worth at 13th lvl I picked up a hammer for the first time. By 15th it was maxed. At 21th I picked up a knife for the first time since about 12th in the time it took me to go from 21st to 22nd in SK my piercing went from a 75 to a 110. I have dwarven base int and a dex of 95/97 holding bullsmasher. I have noticed that I'd sometimes go 2 or 3 fights without seeing a skill increase and then next time I see one it's 5 or so points higher then I remember. You might be getting them just not noticeing it do to spam on your chat screen.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">voards</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">for daryoon, piercing and 1h slash was quickly maxed out, but 2h slash took a long time. i was 11th level before 2h slash caught up, so it will just take time.<P>daryoon</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Ruatha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><I>I've started a Barb Warrior (level 5)...but I am lucky to get 2 skill increases per level with my weapons.</I><P>You've got 3 things working against you here.<P>1) Some skills (notably weapon skills and sense heading) are a real bear to raise before you reach a skill level of 20.<BR>2) The first few levels are fast, so you have a limited amount of time in which to get enough hits in to raise the skill.<BR>3) Barb INT is low, making it hard to raise skills.<P>When you get to a higher level, you'll start maxing the skills out because you'll get more successes per level, giving you more chances to increase the skill.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Ruatha Kneeslasher &lt;Wings of Honor&gt;<BR>40th Level Gnome Warriorette<BR><I>That which does not kill me jolly well won't be getting a second chance.</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Usriev</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Let me suggest that if you want to work piercing or 1H Blunt after level 13 is just to put the weapon in your off hand.  YOu can gain skill while using a different weapon in your off hand.<P>For example,  At level 20, I realized that I wanted to be able to use any weapon that I picked up.  Never know when you are doing the long naked walk if you need a weapon.<P>I was maxed in 1H slash, DW, and DA.  I just bought a FS Dagger (delay 19) put it in my off hand and went to town on the blue cons.  Very slow going til about the skill number 20 and then the fast speed of the dagger really caused a climb.  For 1H Blunt, I used a Screaming Mace, not the fastest, but the proc made up for it.<P>For 2HB, go to Lake Rathe and find the shovel in the orc camp.  Delay 27 Damage 4 will help raise skill a lot.<P>Hofbrau<BR><P>------------------<BR>Hofbrau 23rd Ogre Warrior<BR>Usriev  16th DE Shadowknight</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Jehu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Thanks all<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
